Sister Mary Prema ([[Birth name|n<U+00E9>e]] Mechthild Pierick on May 13, 1953) is the newly elected Superior General of the [[Missionaries of Charity]] of [[Calcutta]]. She will succeed [[Sister Nirmala]] Joshi who relieved herself from the position citing ill-health.

Sister Mary Prema hails from a farming community in [[Reken]], [[Germany]].
